WEBVTT

00:01.520 --> 00:04.034
<i>Even though I was</i>
<i>already an amazing doctor,</i>

00:04.120 --> 00:08.238
<i>when I became chief resident, I decided</i>
<i>to add something extra to my repertoire.</i>

00:08.320 --> 00:09.435
<i>A hook, if you will.</i>

00:09.520 --> 00:13.433
Mrs MacCalla, 40s, moderately
attractive, condition improving.

00:13.520 --> 00:16.033
Did you just say
I was moderately attractive?

00:16.120 --> 00:17.758
Excuse me, Mrs MacCalla.

00:17.840 --> 00:21.230
Patient's complaint of hearing loss
was clearly to get attention.

00:21.320 --> 00:24.835
Where'd you get the idea
for the stupid tape recorder?

00:24.920 --> 00:27.718
<i>Dude, I love</i>
<i>your new tape recorder.</i>

00:29.960 --> 00:31.154
You two are idiots.

00:31.240 --> 00:34.550
Come on, Carla, I wanted a hook,
and I only had one other idea.

00:34.640 --> 00:36.995
Mr Hawkins, the results
of your tests are back,

00:37.080 --> 00:39.753
- and you have...
- Liver disease. Liver disease.

00:39.840 --> 00:41.273
Sorry. That's all he can say.

00:41.360 --> 00:44.511
You don't have liver disease.
You have inoperable lung cancer.

00:44.600 --> 00:47.831
- Liver disease.
- If only, Chauncey.

00:47.920 --> 00:50.878
Bottom line, a recorder won't
fly away and break your heart.

00:50.960 --> 00:54.669
Sorry. I'm just a little edgy because
my husband woke me up last night,

00:54.760 --> 00:57.115
and he knows once I'm up
I can't go back to sleep.

00:57.200 --> 00:58.918
Baby, I was quiet last night.

01:04.160 --> 01:06.355
Great, I'm awake.

01:06.440 --> 01:08.431
Sorry about that, sweetness.

01:08.520 --> 01:10.875
Since you're up,
I was wondering if we could...

01:10.960 --> 01:14.316
Are you crazy?
No, Turk. I...

01:19.680 --> 01:22.353
Gesundheit.
<i>I love my new tape recorder.</i>

01:22.440 --> 01:25.273
<i>Not only is it a timesaver,</i>
<i>I can record my every thought.</i>

01:25.360 --> 01:27.237
I like toast.

01:27.320 --> 01:30.437
<i>They aren't all winners.</i>
<i>Still, as long as I have this thing,</i>

01:30.520 --> 01:32.715
<i>I don't need to be</i>
<i>in my head so much.</i>

01:32.800 --> 01:34.199
Excuse me.

01:34.280 --> 01:36.635
<i>Why did I say excuse me?</i>
<i>He bumped into me.</i>

01:36.720 --> 01:38.597
<i>I have to stop doing that.</i>

01:38.680 --> 01:41.319
Excuse me!
<i>Frick!</i>

01:41.400 --> 01:42.719
Got you a blueberry muffin,

01:42.800 --> 01:45.268
but you don't like blueberries,
so I picked 'em out.

01:45.360 --> 01:48.193
<i>People think Molly's off,</i>
<i>but I totally get her.</i>

01:48.280 --> 01:50.350
<i>She's like the big sister</i>
<i>I always wanted.</i>

01:50.440 --> 01:52.271
<i>She makes me feel</i>
<i>better about myself.</i>

01:52.360 --> 01:55.033
They're so not finger toes.
These are finger toes.

01:55.120 --> 01:57.998
- Yours are cute, like French fries.
- Really?

01:58.080 --> 02:01.436
Yeah. I can do calligraphy with mine.

02:01.520 --> 02:02.953
<i>She looks after me.</i>

02:03.040 --> 02:04.473
Sorry, sorry!

02:09.800 --> 02:12.109
<i>She makes me do things</i>
<i>I don't normally do.</i>

